    {
      "self_ref": "#/texts/34",
      "parent": {
        "cref": "#/groups/1"
      },
      "children": [],
      "content_layer": "body",
      "meta": null,
      "label": "text",
      "prov": [],
      "orig": "PSPO 1089: Incorrect Patient Information Displayed in CPRS V27 (Remedy 283347, 283230, 282836, 275953, 282479, 282175, 281454, 280535, 280286, 279900, 279834, 279461, 279437, 277134, 277814, 275953, 278338, 278521, 278534, 278506, 278354, 278663, 278734, 278621, 278983, 284731, 284653) –",
      "text": "PSPO 1089: Incorrect Patient Information Displayed in CPRS V27 (Remedy 283347, 283230, 282836, 275953, 282479, 282175, 281454, 280535, 280286, 279900, 279834, 279461, 279437, 277134, 277814, 275953, 278338, 278521, 278534, 278506, 278354, 278663, 278734, 278621, 278983, 284731, 284653) –",
      "formatting": {
        "bold": true,
        "italic": false,
        "underline": false,
        "strikethrough": false,
        "script": "baseline"
      },
      "hyperlink": null
    },
    {
      "self_ref": "#/texts/35",
      "parent": {
        "cref": "#/groups/1"
      },
      "children": [],
      "content_layer": "body",
      "meta": null,
      "label": "text",
      "prov": [],
      "orig": "When switching from a patient’s record to a second patient’s record (in the same instance of CPRS) while using CPRS GUI v.27, the first patient’s information may still be displayed in the second patient’s CPRS display, impacting patient care decisions. It is not known at this time if data entered for the second patient will be placed in the incorrect record. This problem occurs intermittently and has been reported when viewing clinical data on the Orders and Notes Tabs.",
      "text": "When switching from a patient’s record to a second patient’s record (in the same instance of CPRS) while using CPRS GUI v.27, the first patient’s information may still be displayed in the second patient’s CPRS display, impacting patient care decisions. It is not known at this time if data entered for the second patient will be placed in the incorrect record. This problem occurs intermittently and has been reported when viewing clinical data on the Orders and Notes Tabs.",
      "formatting": {
        "bold": false,
        "italic": false,
        "underline": false,
        "strikethrough": false,
        "script": "baseline"
      },
      "hyperlink": null
    },
    {
      "self_ref": "#/texts/36",
      "parent": {
        "cref": "#/body"
      },
      "children": [],
      "content_layer": "body",
      "meta": null,
      "label": "text",
      "prov": [],
      "orig": "The PSPO 1089 problem can occur when CPRS tries to shut down due to inactivity and cannot shut down. When this happens, an internal variable (FTimedOut), used by CPRS when it is shutting down, can remain set incorrectly. This condition can cause the previous patient’s data to remain in the chart when switching patients.",
      "text": "The PSPO 1089 problem can occur when CPRS tries to shut down due to inactivity and cannot shut down. When this happens, an internal variable (FTimedOut), used by CPRS when it is shutting down, can remain set incorrectly. This condition can cause the previous patient’s data to remain in the chart when switching patients.",
      "formatting": {
        "bold": false,
        "italic": false,
        "underline": false,
        "strikethrough": false,
        "script": "baseline"
      },
      "hyperlink": null
    },
    {
      "self_ref": "#/texts/37",
      "parent": {
        "cref": "#/body"
      },
      "children": [],
      "content_layer": "body",
      "meta": null,
      "label": "text",
      "prov": [],
      "orig": "There are several possible reasons why the problem occurred.",
      "text": "There are several possible reasons why the problem occurred.",
      "formatting": {
        "bold": false,
        "italic": false,
        "underline": false,
        "strikethrough": false,
        "script": "baseline"
      },
      "hyperlink": null
    },
    {
      "self_ref": "#/texts/38",
      "parent": {
        "cref": "#/body"
      },
      "children": [],
      "content_layer": "body",
      "meta": null,
      "label": "text",
